title.narrative: National capacity to deliver quality primary school education is improved and there is increased availability of quality primary education services.

description.narrative: The enhanced capacity of 1,247 teachers (17% or 211 female) contributed to improved availability and delivery of quality education services across Somalia. A total of 17,155 students participated in student learning assessments (EGRA/EGMA and Monitoring Learning Achievement/MLA) that were conducted in Somaliland and the Federal Member States of Puntland, South West State and Jubaland. These learning achievement findings informed government and Development Partners-supported interventions to improve teaching and learning processes. This together with the management of terminal examinations at the end of primary school (Grade 8), all contributed to improving the education services in the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
